  "prompt": "What are your favourite Bob Dylan lyrics?",
  "response": "Bob Dylan has penned countless memorable lyrics, but a few standouts often admired for their depth and artistry include:\n\n1. **\"The Times They Are a-Changin'\"**: This song captures the spirit of social change and has become an anthem for transformation and progress.\n   \n2. **\"Like a Rolling Stone\"**: Known for its impactful storytelling and raw emotion, these lyrics convey a sense of disillusionment and liberation.\n\n3. **\"Blowin' in the Wind\"**: With its poetic questions about peace, freedom, and human existence, this song is both simple and profound.\n\n4. **\"Tangled Up in Blue\"**: This track features complex narratives and vivid imagery, showcasing Dylan\u2019s skill as a storyteller.\n\n5. **\"It's Alright Ma (I\u2019m Only Bleeding)\"**: A deep dive into existential themes and societal critique, its lyrics are intricate and thought-provoking.\n\nEach of these songs reflects Dylan's unique ability to blend poetry with music, capturing complex emotions and societal issues.",
